    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-21T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5578a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-21T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. La Luz Mining Company, Delaware Corporation, advises Department that it has
                    just received cable via Bragman’s Bluff through Standard Fruit and Steamship
                    Company that Sandino on April 12 raided its mine in the Prinzapolka district,
                    looting all gold bullion, currency, merchandise and animals, and taking all
                    employees of the Company prisoners including the Assistant Superintendent, Mr.
                    George B. Marshall.</p>
                <p>Please cable as soon as possible all information available.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
